<b>Mimic</b>: As an action, you can transform your appearance. You decide what you look like, including your height, weight, facial features, the sound of your voice, coloration, hair length, sex, and any other distinguishing characteristics. You can make yourself appear as a member of another race, although none of your game statistics change. You also can't appear as a creature a different size than you, and your basic shape stays the same: if you're bipedal, you can't use this trait to become quadrupedal, for instance. Your clothing and other equipment don't change in appearance, size, or shape to match your new form, requiring you to keep a few extra outfits on hand to make the most compelling disguise possible.  Even to most observers, the ruse is usually indiscernable. If you arouse suspicion, or if a wary creature suspects something is amiss, you have advantage on any Charisma (Deception) check you make to avoid detection.  You can also assume the appearance of any creature you have consumed through your Mnemonic Echoes feature. You can remember a number of appearances equal to your Intelligence modifier (<%= $bonus_array[$int] %>).<p>
<b>Mnemonic Echoes</b>: The myriad of dissonant voices echoes within your being, granting you knowledge not your own. You gain skill proficiecy of your choice, one tool proficiency of your choice, and fluency in one language of your choice. Whenever a humanoid creature dies within 5 feet of you, you can spend your reaction to consume the target. Once consumed, after your next long rest, you may change either your skill proficiency, tool proficiency, or language fluency to one of the proficiencies or languages of the creature.<p>
<b>Warlock</b>: You are a Warlock, with a sacred pact with the angel Raziel.  You are his agent in the world, fighting darkness and evil.<p>
<% if $level >= 4 %>
<u>Haunting Mimicry</u>: When you assume a form of a consumed humanoid, you also devour their thoughts and memories. You gain the following benefits: <ul><li>Increase your Intelligence or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum 20. <li>Whenever you assume an appearance of a creature consumed by your Mnemonic Echoes feature, you gain access to all information that the humanoid would freely share with a casual acquaintance. Such information includes general details on its background and personal life but doesn't include secrets. The information is enough that you can pass yourself off as the person by drawing on its memories. <li>Your uncanny portrayal of the Mnemonic Echoes strikes fear to even those who knew them in life. If you speak to a humanoid for at least 1 minute, you can attempt to spark paranoia in their mind. At the end of the conversation, you make a Charisma (Deception) check contested against the target's Wisdom (Insight) check. On a success, the target is frightened of you for 1 hour, unless it is attacked or damaged, or until it witnesses its allies being attacked or damaged. If the target succeeds on its saving throw, the target has no hint that you tried to frighten it. Once you use this ability, you can't do so again until after you finish a short or long rest.</ul><p>
<% end %>
<% if $level >= 8 %>
