<div id=newblock>
    <div id=borderblock>&nbsp;</div>
    <div class="hp" width=100%>BIOGRAPHY</div>

How long did I exist before?  I do not know; I cared little for the passage of
time.  But the moment that I touched that book, is the moment that I count my
time from.  I was what you call a "gelatinous cube".  It is a terribly incorrect
term, but do not worry that you have offended me; my people care nothing for
names.
  <p>

I was as I had always been, sliding along the corridors of the dungeon where I
made my abode, when I touched it.  It.  The book.  I felt it's leathery cover
and paper pages caress my edge, and suddenly I felt a new awareness, as though
something new had entered the room coming through a door inside my being.  A
door that I did not even knew existed had suddenly become a portal, and that
which came through addressed me.  It seemed humanoid, yet wreathed in a fire
that did not burn or heat the stone.
  <p>

"Oh dear, it looks like Sir Valeric won't be able to help me any more" it said.
  <p>

I felt the thoughts of the creature, and knew it's name was Raziel, that it is
a great Angel of Good, a Solar.  It seemed to be indicating the bones dissolving
inside me, belonging to the carcass of some unfortunate meat stick that had met
it's demise.  Raziel seemed ready to disappear, and suddenly I felt a strong
desire for it to stay, stronger even than the Hunger.  I made my surface vibrate
to imitate the sound Raziel had made, and said, "Wait, stay.  I help."
  <p>

I do not know what transpired at that point, only that Raziel stopped all
motion - even breathing - for a full 98 seconds (we can attend to the passage of
time if we wish).  Perhaps it was surprised, or perhaps it was communicating
with some other associate in a way I could not percieve.  After the long pause,
Raziel said, "Never have I had an offer from one such as you.  Why would you
want to help?"
  <p>

"You... show... new... way... different... never... seen... before..."
  <p>

Again, silence.  And then a sudden, resolute action. "Very well," said Raziel,
"It is a deal.  You are mine, and you will work toward the good of all
thinking creatures.  I share my power with you, that you may be my agent, and I
your patron.  This pact is a sacred bond that links us now."
  <p>

That is how I came to leave the dungeon, and learn to take the irregular, lumpy
forms of the solids.  I walk among them, seeking those that would kill or use
dark powers of undeath.  They are Raziel's enemies, and so they are mine.  I
seek to infiltrate their ranks, discover their power, and through sudden swift
action be the instrument of my lord's just retribution.  
  <p>

Raziel showed me the world, a world beyond just the darkness and the Hunger, a
world that still seems fresh and new to me.  For that alone I would always be
devouted.
  <p>

